article.headline: Tulane 72, Nicholls St. 70
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- Kevin Sims scored 22 points and Eric Vianney made two free throws with 5 seconds left to lift Tulane to a 72-70 victory over Nicholls State on Saturday. The Green Wave (2-1) led by as many as 11 points in the first half and five in the second, but Nicholls State (1-1) was able to close the gap even further late in the game. Fred Hunter, who led the Colonels with 23 points, made a three-point play to give the Colonels a 69-68 lead with 2:13 remaining. Dominic Friend added free throw to make the score 70-68 with 1:19 left. The Green Wave tied the score 16 seconds later on Sims' two free throws. Neither team would score until Vianney's game-winning free throws. Kris Richard and Robinson Louisme scored 12 points apiece for Tulane, while Louisme added eight rebounds. Ryan Bathie had 16 points for the Colonels and Friend chipped in 14.
